{
  "stem": "14060.9",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "My cousin met me, because I went to the Jewish center, where the Jewish community offices were.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "So he picked me up from there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "He took me home.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "That is my first cousin, Professor Gershon Weiler.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "And he was living together with two friends of his in his parents' flat.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "So they immediately accommodated me.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "And the food they gave me consisted of a slivovitz and some chocolates and whatnot, which was totally wrong for my condition.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "But [LAUGHS] but-- I mean, they were very caring.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "And they looked after me.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "Anyway, a few days later, my uncle-- or a week later-- came down from Budapest. this is the one-- the doctor who survived-- and looked at me and decided to put me straight into hospital, which I violently objected.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "But they x-rayed me, and they found that my lungs had still shadows from my pneumonia, and I was in a weak condition and whatnot.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "And I must go in for a couple of week.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "So I did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "And there I got drip-fed daily.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "And my veins were like an old person's, and they kept on jumping so sometimes they had to stick the needle into me five, six times till they found-- till they got my veins.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "And one day, I just about had enough, and I jumped up.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 60,
      "text": "And I said, no more today.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 61,
      "text": "I said, forget it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 62,
      "text": "I'm not letting you.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 63,
      "text": "Being after the war and such shortage of serums, they give it to an elderly patient there, a non-Jew, in the hospital in Sopron.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 64,
      "text": "And the guy got instantly a heart attack  on it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 65,
      "text": "And the doctor told me afterwards I was very lucky, because if I would have got that bad serum in my condition, I would have not survived it.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
